<p>The pattern on Westlake Lake lakefront calls: gas connector oxidation starts around year 4–5 on Lakeshore Drive addresses. Exterior vent cap dampers show stiffness and partial corrosion by year 5–6. Moisture sensor bars on DLEX models in laundry rooms on the lake side of lakefront homes occasionally show early mineral deposits from the humid microclimate — not as severe as the hard water deposits we see in Tustin Ranch, but present. We document this on every lakefront Westlake Village call and give homeowners a specific re-inspection timeline. On Westlake Island — surrounded by water — we accelerate the timeline by about 12 months.</p>

